INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES ('117', '1', '2013-10-28 12:34:54', '2013-10-28 12:34:54', 'Co-founders Kyle Armstrong, Joshua Koch and Zionsville resident Mark Baltz have recently opened their headquarters for The Tyros, LLC, in downtown Zionsville. The Tyros is a high-tech startup that has developed a web and mobile application that will allow sports officials to collaboratively improve their officiating skills at every level.\r\n\r\n“Having officiated for over 10 years myself, I saw a gaping hole in this vocation. Officials are very professional people, and take their job very seriously, but they’ve never really had the proper tools to be as successful as possible,” Koch said.\r\n\r\nThe Tyros hopes to become a major player in the sports officiating industry at both local and national levels. Baltz, a 24-year veteran NFL official and Zionsville resident, was appointed President and CEO of The Tyros.\r\n\r\n“When I was approached with the idea of a cutting-edge app that would allow officials from any sport, at any level, to have access to better opportunities to learn and grow than I ever had, and that they were going to have those opportunities on their computers, phones and tablets, I immediately knew this was something special,” Baltz said. “I knew we had to get this thing developed and get it to its market because guys like me would have died to have this type of technology in the past.” Screen Shot 2013-04-09 at 2.01.47 PM\r\n\r\nThe Tyros partnered with another Zionsville-based business, Swan Software Solutions, in 2012. Swan has dedicated fifteen of its developers to work specifically with its applications software.\r\n\r\n“We have partnered with Swan Software Solutions specifically to serve as the technical side of our company,” Armstrong said. “Their team is made up of incredibly talented people, and they offer an affordable rate. Our goal is to provide officiating associations who use our applications to improve the training and mentoring of their officials and send consistent messages to their officials with a click of a button.”\r\n\r\nThe Tyros is currently working with related associations such as, the NBA Referees Association, Indiana Officials Association, Indiana Football Officials Association and local high school and college officials associations. The Tyros will continue to expand its catalog of sports-related applications and services in the future. For more information, visit: <a href=\"http://www.thetyros.com/\" target=\"_blank\">www.thetyros.com</a>.', 'Officiating app biz opens', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'officiating-app-biz-opens-2', '', '', '2013-10-28 13:14:19', '2013-10-28 13:14:19', '', '0', 'http://localhost/swanBootstrap/?p=117', '0', 'post', '', '0');
